{
  "stem": "11133.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They left us with hair, and got all their women without any hair, you know?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, the barracks-- I remember that we slept on top of the factory, and it was warm.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We felt good and warm.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But he hadn't had the time, yet, to build any bunks, so we all slept on the floor.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was only later that he-- that they built bunks for us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in this particular place, we shared two to a bunk-- so that was kind of nice to not to have to share with five people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were triple bunks, you know-- three tiers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the distinct memory is that it was warm.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Again, he got us some soup and some coffee, and we each got a round little bowl and a pot-- which my mother still has to this day-- red enamelled pot, enamelled pan.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The pan was for soup, the pot was for coffee-- which, you could call it coffee.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, it was just water, really-- and a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But one of the problems-- you know, we felt safe with Schindler, but one of the problems was that there was really no food.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "At that point, this was towards the end of the war, and supplies were very hard to come by.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We all were kind of sick.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Plaszow, I had had my experiences.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had-- I forgot to say that-- I had contracted scarlet fever, and ended up at the epidemical hospital, where-- which was kind of dangerous at the time, you know, to be sick at all.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But at the hospital, unfortunately, as I got over the scarlet fever, I caught typhoid fever, because there were no sanitary conditions.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I got over the typhoid fever, but that left me with jaundice.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
